{"word":"H5459 - סְגֻלָּה - çᵉgullâh - seg-ool-law' - Jewel","slug":"H5459","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">סְגֻלָּה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>çᵉgullâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>seg-ool-law'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Jewel"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E1;&#x05D2;&#x05DC;&#x05BC;&#x05D4; - s<sup>e</sup>gu&#x0302;lla&#x0302;h</b> - <i>seg-ool-law'</i><p/>Feminine passive participle of an unused root meaning to <i>shut</i> up; <i>wealth</i> (as closely <i>shut</i> up): - jewel, peculiar (treasure), proper good, special."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H5461\">H5461</a>"}]}